  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0da2\u0d82\u0d9c\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dae\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1 \u0d92\u0d9a\u0d9a \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 33\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Chinese mobile phone exports up by 33 million units",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Although China's mobile phone exports fell by 17.7% year-on-year due to the epidemic, it rose to 33.02 million units in January as a result of the new normal of the global epidemic, according to a report by the China Academy of Information and Communication Technology (CAICT).",
        "Chinese companies have released 30 new models in the past month. However, it has decreased by 43.4% compared to the previous year, according to CAICT, a research institute under the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology.",
        "Also, Chinese brands continue to dominate the domestic mobile phone market. It was 25.65 million units, which was 77.7% of the total domestic market value."
      ],
